<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Nolina</i> <i>bigelovii</i> or <i>Nolina</i> <i>parryi</i> is dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>ludoviciana</i>, <i>Coleogyne</i> <i>ramosissima</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>acanthocarpa</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>teretifolia</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>heermannii</i>, <i>Gutierrezia</i> <i>microcephala</i>, <i>Salazaria</i> <i>mexicana</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>mohavensis</i>, <i>Thamnosma</i> <i>montana</i> and <i>Yucca</i> <i>schidigera</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Juniperus</i> <i>californica</i> or <i>Pinus</i> <i>monophylla</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 4 m; canopy is open to intermittent. Herbaceous layer is open to intermittent and grassy. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Nolina parryi</i> > 3% absolute cover in the shrub canopy and evenly distributed over scattered low shrubs and herbs (Keeler-Wolf et al. 1998b, Thomas et al. 2004).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Slopes and ridges. Soils are rocky, derived from bedrock or colluvium, with substrates largely granitic or crystalline metamorphics, including calcareous substrates.  </div>
</div>

        
