<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Natural disturbance appears as occasional fires with varied effects. A related species ( <i>Nolina microcarpa</i>) crown sprouts from a caudex in light-severity fires; however, the thick thatch of leaves, which develops on older plants, tends to increase heat, and older plants easily succumb to moderate to severe fires (Griffith 1991d). Some <i>N. bigelovii </i>survived a recent fire in Joshua Tree National Park, while many plants with relatively mature trunks and accumulated thatch died (R. Minnich, pers. comm. 2000).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
